Claimant Count and Universal Credit in Trafford

Claimant Count in Trafford

The Claimant Count indicates the number of people claiming benefits principally for the reason of being unemployed. The Claimant Count in July 2022 was 30.6% higher than in January 2020. The rate of claimants to residents aged 16 to 64 reached 3.1% in July 2022 representing an increment of 0.8% from January 2020. The number of claimants has been decreasing from April 2021.

Change in the Claimant Count for Trafford

The Trafford ward with the largest share of claims in July 2022 was Clifford with 11.9% of all claimants within Trafford. All the wards have less claims in July 2022 compared to July 2021. Clifford has the largest reduction in number of claims with -220 followed by Bucklow-St Martins (-190), Longford (-155) and St Marys (-145).

Change in the Claimant Count for Trafford's wards

The wards with higher claimant rate in July 2022 were Clifford and Gorse Hill with 6.1% and 5.8% respectively. There is a gap of 1.6% between the top five wards on claimant rate and the rest of the wards. The wards where the claimant rate has decreased more from July 2021 to July 2022 are Bucklow-St Martins and Clifford with a decrease in rate of -3.1% and -2.5% respectively followed by St Marys with -1.9%.

In Trafford from July 2021 to July 2022 all age bands have reduced their claimant count. When considering the reduction of claims the age band 18-24 years had the largest reduction with -490 less claims.

Change in the Claimant Count by age bands in Trafford
Change in the Claimant Count by broad age bands in Trafford

At the start of 2020 the age band 25-34 already had the highest number of claims, however after the effects of the Covid-19 pandemic which started in March 2020 this figure increased more sharply compared to the other age bands. The claimant rate as a proportion of Traffords population within each age band shows a higher increase in the age bands of 16-24 and 25-34 compared to the others. The rate and count have been decreasing during the last months for all age bands particularly for the the age bands of 16-24 and 25-34.

Almost half of Traffords claimants are residents of five of the 21 wards. Almost half of the claimants are under 34 years.

Claimant Count for Trafford's wards by age band

Universal Credit claims in Trafford

The Universal Credit claims in Trafford have increased 76.6% from January 2020 to July 2022. The rate of claims as a proportion of people age 16 to 64 increased form 6.1% to 10.8%.

Change in the Universal Credit claims for Trafford

The Trafford MSOA with the largest share of claims in July 2022 was Old Trafford with 11.8% of all Universal Credit claims in Trafford. All but two of the MSOAs have less claims in July 2022 compared to July 2021. The MSOAs that increased the number of claims from July 2021 to July 2022 were Gorse Hill with 20 and Partington with 10. The MSOAs with more reduction in claims when comparing July 2021 to July 2022 are Firswood (-88), Ashton upon Mersey North (-88) and Broadheath & Firsway (-78). The MSOA with more reduction in percentage change from July 2021 to July 2022 was Timperley South with -25% change.

Change in the Universal Credit claims for Trafford's MSOAs

The MSOAs with higher rates of Universal Credit claims in July 2022 were Partington with 26.6% and Old Trafford with 23.5%. The MSOAs where the rate of Universal Credit claims has increased from July 2021 to July 2022 were Gorse Hill with 0.3% and Partington with 0.2%. The MSOA where the rate of Universal Credit claims has decreased more from July 2021 to July 2022 was Ashton upon Mersey North with -2.3%

In Trafford from July 2021 to July 2022 the Over 65 age band has the largest increment in percentage change of Universal Credit claims with 39%. When considering the number of additional claims from July 2021 to July 2022 the 5-year age band 35-39 years had the highest with 104 more claims. The age bands 20-24 and 25-29 have the largest decrease in number of Universal Credit claims.

Change in the Universal Credit claims by age band for Trafford

Following the start of the Covid-19 pandemic in March 2020 the number of claims for all ages rose dramatically from pre-pandemic levels at a similar proportion for all age bands with the age band 16-24 rising faster in May 2020. At the start of 2020 the age band 25-34 had the highest number of claims and also the highest rate maintaining that position after the rise from March 2020 until May 2022 when the 35-44 became the age band with the highest number of claims. The age band 16-24 has the lowest number of claims among the other age bands from July 2021. All the age bands are slightly increasing their levels although the age bands 16-24 and 25-34 have been decreasing more rapidly on rate and number of claims from April 2021.

The Conditionality regimen for entitlement to Universal Credit is associated to work-related things that claimants will have to do to maintain elegibility. In Trafford the largest proportion of Universal Credit claims are in the Searching for Work category however there is also a significant proportion of claims under No work requirements.
